1. Clone the repo
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/usb-device-blocker.git
cd usb-device-blocker
2. Enable and start usbguard
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo systemctl enable usbguard
sudo systemctl start usbguard
3. Create whitelist of approved devices
List currently connected devices:

bash
Copy
Edit
usbguard list-devices | grep present
Copy the ID field (e.g. 0781:5567) for devices you trust.

Edit the allowed_usb.txt file and add each trusted ID on a separate line.

4. Run the blocker
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo python3 usbblocker.py
The script will continuously monitor connected USB devices and block any that aren't on the whitelist.
